MODULE: src/bot
FILES: telegram.js, commands/index.js, commands/registry.js, commands/parser.js, commands/validator.js, commands/formatter.js, commands/help.js
RESPONSIBILITY: Telegram bot setup and command routing system

KEY_FILES:
- telegram.js: bot creation, middleware setup, message handling
- commands/registry.js: command registration and lookup
- commands/parser.js: parse user input into command + args
- commands/validator.js: validate command permissions and args
- commands/formatter.js: format output for Telegram MarkdownV2
- commands/handlers/: one handler per command (alias, audit, bugfix, cat, cd, cli, commit, commits, cron, download, find, head, history, jobs, kill, logs, ls, monitor, more, pipeline, plan, planner, ps, sessions, status, stop, sysinfo, tail, tree, upload, watch)

INTERFACES:
- createTelegramBot(): creates and configures Telegraf bot
- CommandRegistry: register/lookup/list commands
- parseCommand(text): { command, args }
- validateCommand(cmd, ctx): boolean

DEPENDENCIES:
- uses: telegraf: bot framework
- imports: src/services: business logic for command execution
- imports: src/security: permission checks

TRAPS:
- planner.js delegates to pipeline.js but must map type='planner' to type='feature' | FIX: handlePlanner sets params.type='feature' before calling handlePipeline
- pipeline.js metadata enum must match script-runner PIPELINE_TYPES | FIX: Remove unsupported 'planner' from params.type.enum

RULES:
- MUST: All command handlers delegating to pipeline.js must use supported types (feature/bugfix only)
- PREFER: Use type mapping in delegating handlers rather than modifying pipeline infrastructure

CHANGELOG:
- 2026-03-21 | F-016: Fix planner command type mapping bug

UPDATED: 2026-03-21
